																			style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333333; font-size: 12px; text-align: justify;">Last
																			month, we discussed as to why it makes sense to keep
																			your finances simple and uncomplicated in “Keep It
																			Simple Stupid”…. <br /> <br /> As an extension of
																			this, a client shared with us a product, which though
																			falls under the category of a Structured Product,
																			looked promising than any other normal Plain Jane
																			products like Mutual Funds, Fixed Deposits, etc.<br />
																			<br /> <strong>This is what the product
																				pitch says: </strong> <br /> The product gives the investor
																			a chance to earn an interest of 16% p.a., with 100%
																			capital protection. Only condition is that the Nifty
																			should have appreciated by atleast 10% &nbsp;at
																			specified target dates. <br /> <br /> It works like
																			this, starting from the 15th month, on the 1st of
																			every 3rd month (15th month, 18th month, 21st
																			month... 36th month) Nifty levels will be
																			checked.&nbsp;If at any time Nifty has appreciated by
																			over 10%, the scheme concludes and 3 months from that
																			date the investment along with a predefined fixed
																			return is paid back. The chart below explains in
																			detail how much will be paid back, depending on when
																			the target is hit. <br /> <br /> The maximum tenure
																			is 40 months i.e. 3.3 years. The minimum investment
																			to be made is Rs.20 lacs. Investment fee of 3% has to
																			be paid over and above the investment amount ie., for
																			an investment of Rs. 20 lacs, you will have to pay
																			Rs.20.6 lacs.<br /> <br /> <strong>Investor
																				perception</strong> <br /> 16% sounds too appealing to be
																			ignored and one would probably not hesitate to take
																			some risk here. If Nifty has moved up by 10% on any
																			of these target dates, you get your 16% per annum,
																			and Bingo! You are home with returns higher than any
																			FD or FMP in the market. If not, your capital is 100%
																			protected. Cool! <br /> <br /> In a situation,
																			where investors are facing a double whammy due to the
																			falling interest rates and equity markets also show
																			no signs of budging from the current range, this
																			product looks like an angel in disguise! <br /> <br />
																			<strong>Our analysis</strong> <br /> A little bit of
																			analysis and we discovered that “All that Glitters is
																			probably not Gold.” Though prima facie, the returns
																			look attractive @ 16% p.a., the CAGR at any level
																			would not be more than 11.8% p.a. as shown below!<br />
